=== TASK ===
# Search & Filter

## Overview
Implement a fast, contextual search across studies, uploaded materials, and help docs with advanced filtering, suggestions, and secure results. Provide responsive UI with autocomplete, recent/trending query suggestions, facets (child, subject, style, date, starred), and pagination. Ensure search respects ownership and sharing permissions. Integrate with pages page_p005, page_p009, and page_p013 within StudySpark, and align with the app’s playful, kid-friendly design language.

## Components to Build
- SearchBar with Autocomplete
  - Features: real-time query suggestions, recent queries, trending topics, keyboard navigation, accessibility (ARIA), voice input toggle (optional).
  - Data sources: Elasticsearch/Postgres FTS results, recent queries store, trending topics service.
  - UI: input with rounded pill, dropdown with suggestions, quick filters chips.
- Faceted Filter Drawer/Sidebar
  - Facets: Studies/topics, uploaded materials, help docs; sub-facets: child (age group), subject, style, date range, starred/favorite, ownership visibility.
  - UI: collapsible sections, pill-shaped toggles, multi-select, clear all, apply/reset actions.
- Results Grid/List
  - Card-based results with left-aligned metadata (title, snippet), right-aligned quick actions (open, save, share), and visual indicators for type (study/material/help).
  - Include safe rendering for null data; guard array methods.
- Suggestions & Relevance Tunnel
  - Relevance tuning hooks: boost for owned/shared results, user-specific context from child age/style.
  - Autocomplete suggestions: recent queries, trending topics, contextual completions from current query.
- Pagination & Infinite Scrolling
  - Server-side pagination with limit/offset; optional infinite scroll for long results with graceful loading indicators.
- Result Detail Preview Panel
  - Quick view modal or side panel showing study/material/help excerpt with actions to edit, approve, or request changes (for study content).
- Permissions & Ownership Guard
  - Ensure results only display items user has access to; empty/improper results show friendly messages.
- Analytics & Telemetry
  - Track searches, filters used, time-to-result, click-throughs, and conversion to saved studies.
- Integration Points
  - Connect to API layer, user profiles, study/material metadata, and help docs index.
- Accessibility & Internationalization
  - Keyboard navigable components, screen-reader friendly announcements, i18n-ready strings.

## Implementation Requirements

### Frontend
- Frameworks/Tech: React (with hooks), TypeScript, and a state management approach (e.g., React Context or Zustand) if needed.
- Components & Pages to Create
  - SearchBar.tsx
    - Props: onSubmit(query), onSelectSuggestion(suggestion)
    - State: query string, isOpen, suggestions array, highlightedIndex
    - Guard data: uses data ?? [] safely and validates with Array.isArray()
  - FilterDrawer.tsx
    - Props: facets, onApply(filters), onClear()
    - State: selectedFacets, isOpen
    - Ensure all arrays are initialized with [] and guarded
  - ResultsGrid.tsx / ResultsList.tsx
    - Props: results: ResultItem[], total: number, loading: boolean
    - Use: Array.isArray(results) ? results.map(...) : []
  - ResultCard.tsx
    - Props: item: ResultItem
    - Safe access with optional chaining
  - SuggestionsPanel.tsx
    - Props: suggestions: SuggestionItem[]
  - PaginationControls.tsx
    - Props: page, pageSize, total, onPageChange
  - PreviewPanel.tsx
    - Props: item: ResultItem
  - API Hook: useSearch.ts
    - Returns: { data: ResultItem[], total: number, loading: boolean, error?: string }
    - Guard API response shapes: Array.isArray(data) ? data : []
  - utilities
    - safeMap, safeFilter helpers or inline guards: (items ?? []).map(...)
    - formatDate, highlightSnippet utilities
- Data Handling
  - Use data ?? [] for any Supabase results; guard against nulls.
  - Initialize useState with proper types: useState<ResultItem[]>([]) and useState<Facet[]>([]) etc.
  - Validate API responses before rendering: const list = Array.isArray(response?.data) ? response.data : []
- UI/UX Details
  - Card design: rounded corners, soft shadows, pastel gradients, icons.
  - Hover/active states: elevated shadow, subtle glow.
  - Chips/badges: pill-shaped for facets, with color cues per facet type.
  - Loading states: skeletons or shimmer with accessible ARIA live regions.
- Performance
  - Debounce search input to reduce requests.
  - Parallelize facet counts retrieval if needed but guard nulls.
  - Use memoization where appropriate (e.g., derived filters).
- Security & Permissions (Frontend)
  - Do not render items user cannot access; show placeholder when none available.
  - Do not leak private data in previews without authorization.

### Backend
- APIs
  - POST /api/search
    - Accept: { query: string, filters: Filters, page: number, limit: number, sort?: string }
    - Response: { data: ResultItem[], total: number }
  - GET /api/search/suggestions
    - Accept: { query: string }
    - Response: { suggestions: SuggestionItem[], recentlyUsed?: string[] }
  - GET /api/search/facets
    - Response: { facets: { children: string[], subjects: string[], styles: string[], dates: string[] }, counts: { [facetKey]: number } }
  - Security: Enforce ownership and sharing permissions on server-side; do not return items without access.
- Data Models
  - ResultItem
    - id: string
    - type: 'study' | 'material' | 'help'
    - title: string
    - snippet: string
    - ownerId: string
    - sharedWith: string[] // user ids or group ids
    - subject: string | null
    - childAgeGroup: string | null
    - style: string | null
    - createdAt: string
    - updatedAt: string
    - isStarred?: boolean
    - url?: string
  - SuggestionItem
    - text: string
    - type: 'query' | 'topic' | 'recent'
  - Filters
    - query: string
    - facets: { child?: string[], subject?: string[], style?: string[], starred?: boolean, dateFrom?: string, dateTo?: string }
    - ownership?: 'private' | 'shared' | 'all'
- Search Engine
  - Use Elasticsearch or Postgres Full-Text Search (FTS)
  - Relevancy scoring: boost owned/shared results, user context, and freshness
  - Autocomplete: edge n-gram or completion fields; fuzzy search tolerance
  - Suggestion logic: recentQueries, trendingTopics, and query-typed completions
- Validation
  - Validate inputs server-side: non-empty strings, valid date formats, arrays of strings.
  - Ensure results always have a finite total; handle zero gracefully.
- Performance & Scaling
  - Indexing strategy for studies, materials, and help docs with uniform fields for search.
  - Caching layer for trending topics and recently used suggestions if available.
  - Rate limiting, input sanitization to prevent injection.

### Integration
- Data Flow
  - Frontend SearchBar captures query -> useSearch hook -> /api/search -> results -> ResultsGrid cards -> PreviewPanel on select.
  - FilterDrawer updates filters -> triggers new /api/search with updated params.
  - SuggestionsPanel consumes /api/search/suggestions for autocomplete.
  - Facet data fetched via /api/search/facets to populate filters with counts.
- State Management
  - Global search state includes currentQuery, activeFilters, currentPage, results, total, loading.
  - Synchronize with route params (optional) for shareable search URLs.
- Error Handling
  - Graceful handling of network errors; show friendly messages and retry options.
  - Ensure UI remains stable if API returns malformed data; apply default safe values.

## User Experience Flow
1. User lands on the Search page within page_p005/page_p009/page_p013.
2. User begins typing in the SearchBar.
   - Autocomplete suggests recent queries, trending topics, and contextual completions.
   - Users can select a suggestion or continue typing.
3. User toggles Filters via the FilterDrawer.
   - Facets show counts; user selects multiple facets (child, subject, style, date range, starred).
   - Clear All and Apply actions update the results.
4. Results render as a grid/list with cards showing title, snippet, type, and metadata.
   - Results respect ownership and sharing permissions; unauthorized items are omitted.
5. User clicks a result to open a PreviewPanel with more details and actions (save, edit, or request changes for studies).
6. User can paginate or infinite-scroll to view more results.
7. On empty results, show friendly guidance and optional tips to broaden filters or search terms.
8. User interactions are saved for future sessions (recent queries, preferred filters).

